strokes. Σ and Ε are lunate, the latter with a short middle bar; Ν has a rounded join between the second and third strokes; Α has a slight apex, and a horizontal bar; Π has vertical hastae of equal length, and the cross-bar overlaps slightly on both sides; Ρ is not quite closed, with a well-rounded eye; the vertical stroke of Φ extends up to join the base of the letter on the line above. Interpuncts are used regularly to mark word-breaks and have the form of a comma.",[37,46],{"type":38,"l":39,"from":40,"to":41,"h":42,"unit":43,"atLeast":44,"atMost":45},"letterHeight","Lines 1-5","line1","line5","56-63","mm","56","63",{"type":47,"l":48,"from":40,"to":49,"h":50,"unit":43},"interlinear","Interlineation","line2","not measured",{"_":52,"notBefore":53,"notAfter":54,"evidence":55},"Second half of 2nd century CE",151,200,"context",[57,62],{"_":58,"type":59,"ref":60,"region":61},"Halaesa","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462225","Sicilia",{"_":63,"type":64,"ref":65,"offset":66,"region":61},"Castel di Tusa","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525099","near",[68],[69,70],37.99907,14.26197,[],"Sicily",{"_":74,"role":75,"ref":76},"Antiquarium e sito archeologico di Halaesa ","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/053",{"_":78,"type":79},"30602","inventory",{"_":81,"mainLang":82,"languages":83},"Ancient Greek","grc",[81],"645670",{"n":86,"url":87,"height":88,"width":89,"desc":90,"surfaceType":91},"screen","ISic003591_tiled.tif","3680px","4872px","Photo J.Prag courtesy Soprintendenza BBCCAA di Messina","front",[93],{"atLeast":94,"atMost":95},56,63,[97,98,99],"Scibona, 2008, Alesa Archonidea dalla riscoperta tardo rinascimentale agli scavi del XX secolo","Scibona, 2009, L'Agorà (scavi 1970-2004)","Prag, Tigano, 2017, Alesa Archonidea: il lapidarium",[101,102,103],"JX9IX97G","DSZEF4K5","MI64NB9L",[105,106,107,15,19,108,109,110,111,112,109,113,114,82],"isic003591","honours for aelius asinius petitus, rhetor",{"_":12},"marble","halaesa","castel di tusa","sicilia","